# RheXa Backend Environment Configuration

## Environment Variables Template

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your values.

```env
# ============================================
# SUPABASE (Database & Auth)
# ============================================

# Supabase credentials (get from Supabase Dashboard > Settings > API)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key

# ============================================
# PINECONE (Vector Database)
# ============================================

PINECONE_API_KEY=your-pinecone-api-key
PINECONE_INDEX_NAME=rhexa-vectors

# ============================================
# STRIPE (Payments)
# ============================================

STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_xxx
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxx
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_xxx

# ============================================
# RESEND (Emails)
# ============================================

RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxx

# ============================================
# APPLICATION SETTINGS
# ============================================

# Application name
APP_NAME=RheXa API

# Environment: development, staging, production
ENV=development

# Debug mode (false in production)
DEBUG=false

# ============================================
# SECURITY
# ============================================

# Secret key for JWT token signing (min 32 characters, use secrets.token_urlsafe(32))
SECRET_KEY=your-super-secret-key-here-minimum-32-characters

# JWT algorithm
ALGORITHM=HS256

# Token expiration in minutes (7 days = 10080 minutes)
ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=10080

# Encryption key for sensitive data (min 32 characters)
ENCRYPTION_KEY=your-encryption-key-here-minimum-32-characters

# CORS allowed origins (comma separated)
CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:8000,https://yourdomain.com

# ============================================
# DATABASE
# ============================================

# MySQL
# DATABASE_URL=mysql+pymysql://user:password@localhost:3306/rhexa_db

# PostgreSQL (Recommended for production)
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/rhexa_db

# For production, use environment variable or secrets management
DATABASE_URL=

# Database connection pool settings
DB_POOL_SIZE=10
DB_MAX_OVERFLOW=20
DB_POOL_TIMEOUT=30
DB_POOL_RECYCLE=3600

# ============================================
# AI & LANGUAGE MODELS
# ============================================

# OpenAI API Key (for embeddings and fallback)
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-

# OpenAI embedding model
EMBEDDING_MODEL=text-embedding-3-small

# OpenRouter API Key (primary LLM)
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-

# OpenRouter model (free tier option)
OPENROUTER_MODEL=stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free

# Hugging Face token (for models)
HF_TOKEN=

# ============================================
# VECTOR DATABASE & RAG
# ============================================

# Path to vector store directory
VECTOR_DB_PATH=vector_store

# Chunk size for document splitting (characters)
CHUNK_SIZE=1000

# Overlap between chunks (characters)
CHUNK_OVERLAP=200

# Temperature for LLM responses (0.0-2.0)
LLM_TEMPERATURE=0.7

# ============================================
# EXTERNAL INTEGRATIONS
# ============================================

# Google OAuth
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=
GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/auth/google/callback

# GitHub OAuth
GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=
GITHUB_REDIRECT_URI=http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/auth/github/callback

# Frontend URL (for redirects and CORS)
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000

# ============================================
# EMAIL (Optional)
# ============================================

# SMTP Configuration
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASSWORD=your-app-specific-password

# Email from address
EMAILS_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@rhexa.com
EMAILS_FROM_NAME=RheXa Security

# ============================================
# LOGGING
# ============================================

# Log level: DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR, CRITICAL
LOG_LEVEL=INFO

# Log file path
LOG_FILE=logs/rhexa.log

# ============================================
# UPLOAD SETTINGS
# ============================================

# Maximum upload file size (bytes) - 50MB default
MAX_UPLOAD_SIZE=52428800

# Allowed file extensions (comma separated)
ALLOWED_EXTENSIONS=pdf,txt,csv,xlsx,docx

# Upload directory
UPLOAD_DIR=uploads

# ============================================
# STORAGE (Cloud storage optional)
# ============================================

# S3/MinIO Configuration
S3_ENDPOINT_URL=
S3_ACCESS_KEY=
S3_SECRET_KEY=
S3_BUCKET_NAME=rhexa-uploads

# ============================================
# MONITORING & OBSERVABILITY
# ============================================

# Sentry DSN for error tracking (optional)
SENTRY_DSN=

# Datadog API key (optional)
DATADOG_API_KEY=

# ============================================
# WORKER SETTINGS (Production)
# ============================================

# Number of Gunicorn workers (CPU cores * 2 + 1)
WORKERS=4

# Maximum requests before worker restart
MAX_REQUESTS=1000

# Request jitter
MAX_REQUESTS_JITTER=50

# Worker timeout (seconds)
WORKER_TIMEOUT=60

# ============================================
# CACHE SETTINGS
# ============================================

# Redis URL for caching (optional)
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379/0

# Cache TTL in seconds
CACHE_TTL=3600

# ============================================
# RATE LIMITING
# ============================================

# Enable rate limiting
ENABLE_RATE_LIMIT=true

# Requests per minute
RATE_LIMIT_REQUESTS=100

# ============================================
# DEVELOPER SETTINGS
# ============================================

# Enable detailed error messages
DETAILED_ERRORS=false

# Enable query logging
QUERY_LOGGING=false

# Reload on code changes
AUTO_RELOAD=false
```

## 🔑 How to Generate Secrets

### Secret Key
```bash
# Python
python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))"

# OpenSSL
openssl rand -base64 32
```

### Encryption Key
```bash
# Python
python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"

# OpenSSL
openssl rand -hex 32
```

## 🔐 Security Best Practices

1. **Never commit `.env` to git** - Use `.env.example` instead
2. **Use strong secrets** - Minimum 32 characters
3. **Rotate secrets regularly** - At least quarterly
4. **Use environment variables** - Don't hardcode secrets
5. **Use secrets management** - AWS Secrets Manager, HashiCorp Vault, etc.
6. **Restrict file permissions** - `chmod 600 .env`

## 🌍 Environment-Specific Configurations

### Development (.env.development)
```env
ENV=development
DEBUG=true
DATABASE_URL=mysql+pymysql://root:password@localhost:3306/rhexa_dev
LOG_LEVEL=DEBUG
QUERY_LOGGING=true
```

### Staging (.env.staging)
```env
ENV=staging
DEBUG=false
LOG_LEVEL=INFO
```

### Production (.env.production)
```env
ENV=production
DEBUG=false
LOG_LEVEL=WARNING
# Use secrets manager for sensitive values
```

## 📝 Default Values

These are omitted from `.env` and use defaults:

| Variable | Default |
|----------|---------|
| `ALGORITHM` | `HS256` |
| `ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES` | `10080` (7 days) |
| `EMBEDDING_MODEL` | `text-embedding-3-small` |
| `OPENROUTER_MODEL` | `stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free` |
| `CHUNK_SIZE` | `1000` |
| `CHUNK_OVERLAP` | `200` |
| `SMTP_PORT` | `587` |
| `DB_POOL_SIZE` | `10` |
| `MAX_UPLOAD_SIZE` | `52428800` (50MB) |

